<BR>
Excerpt from "The Great Hunt" by Robert Jordan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthoricofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric of Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Uber Gimp</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/18/00 9:35:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cobalt Armor...</span><hr size=1> Well, first thing, you'll need to be around 50 or its hard to get a group for even the easiest to find bits. Here's where they drop and what level/quest you need to get to the dungeon. <br>
<br>
Karnor's Castle-<br>
Lvl: 49+<br>
No quest required for entry<br>
This is the easiest dungeon in Kunark to get to from your home city in Firiona Vie.<br>
<br>
Drops:<br>
Cobalt Gauntlets-Off the Drolvang Captain. This mob spawns early in the zone, and is often pulled by groups camping the zone or front corners. Generally one to two pair will drop a day. Best bet, get in the tower group, as this is where he spawns. <br>
<br>
Cobalt Boots-Off one of the mobs in back left of top floor, i think its the Caller of Sathir. Pullable to zone, and often is, but best bet is to get a group for the back courtyard and camp it. <br>
<br>
Cobalt Legs-Off of Venril Sathir himself. Noone on Brell has killed him to date. Strategies have been discussed, but require more 56+ warriors monks and rogues than are available at this time. <br>
<br>
Old Sebilis-<br>
Level-52+ <br>
Quest required to get key to enter dungeon-kill froglok hunter and forager and take the medallions they drop to the ghost of Emperor in crypt along zone wall to right of zone from swamp of no hope. <br>
<br>
Cobalt Vambraces-Drop off one of the frogloks by disco room. easiest bit to get in sebilis.<br>
<br>
Cobalt Bracer-Drops off random myconids on the lower level. Generally requires at least 12 people to camp this area, much like the efreeti raids of old. Levels 53+ preferred.<br>
<br>
Cobalt Helm-Drops off Reet Frogloks on way to Trakanon's lair. Requires a raid group of 18 people or so to break in, less to hold. Levels 53+ preferred.<br>
<br>
Cobalt BP-Drops off Trakanon himself. Noone has killed him on Brell to date. That may change soon...<br>
<br>
Anyway, there's the brief guide to cobalt armor. <br>
<br>
Thoric Frosthammer<br>
Silent Redemption <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tembdaraangelknight>Tembdara AngelKnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/18/00 7:10:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cobalt Armor...</span><hr size=1> From what I've seen and done to date in Kunark I think my chances of getting Indicolite in Hate are better than Cobalt right now. <br>
